  "title": "Service Engineer (Scientific & Analytical Analyzer)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Install, calibrate, and commission Particle Size Analyzers, XRF instruments, and Spectroscopy devices at customer sites.</li>\n  <li>Perform preventive maintenance on analytical and scientific equipment to ensure reliability and accurate results.</li>\n  <li>Troubleshoot, diagnose, and repair any equipment faults or performance issues promptly.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all work complies with industry standards and quality procedures.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Engineering</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of experience in servicing semiconductor instruments.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of laboratory analytical techniques, including <strong>spectroscopy, XRF, and particle size analysis.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
